Creating a **smooth Snake game in C** that uses **images for animation** and supports a **whole level** is a great project that combines **graphics programming**, **game loop logic**, and **image handling**. Below is a step-by-step guide to help you build this game using **C**, **graphics libraries**, and **image animation**.

---

## 🧩 1. **Choose a Graphics Library**

To make the game smooth and use images, you'll need a graphics library. Here are some options:

### ✅ Recommended: **SDL2 (Simple DirectMedia Layer)**
- Cross-platform
- Easy to use for 2D games
- Supports image loading and animation
- Has a good community and documentation

You can install SDL2 via package managers or from source.

**Install SDL2 on Linux:**
```bash
sudo apt-get install libsdl2-dev
```

**Install SDL2 on Windows:**
- Download from [https://www.libsdl.org/download-2.0.php](https://www.libsdl.org/download-2.0.php)
- Follow the installation instructions for Windows

---

## 🧱 2. **Project Structure**

Your project will have the following components:

- `main.c` – Main game loop
- `snake.c` – Snake logic
- `level.c` – Level and image loading
- `graphics.c` – SDL2 initialization and rendering
- `images/` – Folder for your snake, food, and background images

---

## 🐍 3. **Basic Game Components**

### 3.1. **Game Loop**
The game loop handles:
- Input
- Game logic (movement, collision)
- Rendering

```c
while (running) {
    handle_input();
    update_game();
    render_frame();
    SDL_Delay(1000 / FPS); // Control frame rate
}
```

### 3.2. **Snake Structure**
```c
typedef struct {
    SDL_Point *body;
    int length;
    SDL_Texture *texture;
    int direction;
} Snake;
```

### 3.3. **Level and Images**
You can load images for:
- Snake body
- Food
- Background
- Level tiles (if using tile-based levels)

Use `SDL_LoadBMP` or `SDL_LoadPNG` to load images.

---

## 🖼️ 4. **Image Animation**

To animate the snake, you can use **sprite sheets** or **multiple images** for each segment of the snake.

### 4.1. Load Image
```c
SDL_Texture *load_texture(SDL_Renderer *renderer, const char *path) {
    SDL_Surface *surface = SDL_LoadBMP(path);
    if (!surface) {
        SDL_Log("Failed to load image: %s", SDL_GetError());
        return NULL;
    }
    SDL_Texture *texture = SDL_CreateTextureFromSurface(renderer, surface);
    SDL_FreeSurface(surface);
    return texture;
}
```

### 4.2. Animate Snake
Use a frame counter to cycle through different images for each segment.

```c
void render_snake(SDL_Renderer *renderer, Snake *snake, SDL_Texture *body_texture, SDL_Texture *head_texture) {
    for (int i = 0; i < snake->length; i++) {
        SDL_Rect dest;
        dest.x = snake->body[i].x * TILE_SIZE;
        dest.y = snake->body[i].y * TILE_SIZE;
        dest.w = TILE_SIZE;
        dest.h = TILE_SIZE;

        if (i == 0) { // Head
            SDL_RenderCopy(renderer, head_texture, NULL, &dest);
        } else {
            SDL_RenderCopy(renderer, body_texture, NULL, &dest);
        }
    }
}
```

---

## 🧩 5. **Level and Background**

To support a full level, you can:
- Load a level map (e.g., a 2D array)
- Use tile images for background
- Load a background image or tileset

### 5.1. Load Level Map
```c
int **load_level(const char *filename, int *rows, int *cols) {
    FILE *file = fopen(filename, "r");
    if (!file) return NULL;

    fscanf(file, "%d %d", rows, cols);
    int **map = malloc(*rows * sizeof(int *));
    for (int i = 0; i < *rows; i++) {
        map[i] = malloc(*cols * sizeof(int));
        for (int j = 0; j < *cols; j++) {
            fscanf(file, "%d", &map[i][j]);
        }
    }
    fclose(file);
    return map;
}
```

### 5.2. Render Level
```c
void render_level(SDL_Renderer *renderer, int **level, int rows, int cols, SDL_Texture *tile_texture) {
    for (int y = 0; y < rows; y++) {
        for (int x = 0; x < cols; x++) {
            int tile = level[y][x];
            if (tile == 0) continue; // Empty space
            SDL_Rect dest = {x * TILE_SIZE, y * TILE_SIZE, TILE_SIZE, TILE_SIZE};
            SDL_RenderCopy(renderer, tile_texture, NULL, &dest);
        }
    }
}
```

---

## 🎮 6. **Game Logic**

### 6.1. Movement
Update the snake's position based on direction.

```c
void update_snake(Snake *snake, int direction) {
    SDL_Point new_head = {snake->body[0].x + direction_x[direction], snake->body[0].y + direction_y[direction]};
    // Check for collision
    if (check_collision(new_head, snake)) {
        game_over = true;
        return;
    }
    // Add new head
    SDL_realloc(snake->body, (snake->length + 1) * sizeof(SDL_Point));
    snake->body[snake->length++] = new_head;
    // Remove tail if not eating
    if (!eaten_food) {
        SDL_memmove(snake->body, snake->body + 1, (snake->length - 1) * sizeof(SDL_Point));
    }
}
```

### 6.2. Collision Detection
Check for wall or self collision.

```c
bool check_collision(SDL_Point point, Snake *snake) {
    // Check wall
    if (point.x < 0 || point.x >= LEVEL_WIDTH || point.y < 0 || point.y >= LEVEL_HEIGHT) return true;
    // Check self
    for (int i = 1; i < snake->length; i++) {
        if (point.x == snake->body[i].x && point.y == snake->body[i].y) return true;
    }
    return false;
}
```

---

## 🎨 7. **Putting It All Together**

### 7.1. Main Function
```c
int main(int argc, char *argv[]) {
    SDL_Init(SDL_INIT_VIDEO);
    SDL_Window *window = SDL_CreateWindow("Snake Game", SDL_WINDOWPOS_CENTERED, SDL_WINDOWPOS_CENTERED, SCREEN_WIDTH, SCREEN_HEIGHT, 0);
    SDL_Renderer *renderer = SDL_CreateRenderer(window, -1, SDL_RENDERER_ACCELERATED);

    // Load images
    SDL_Texture *snake_texture = load_texture(renderer, "snake.bmp");
    SDL_Texture *food_texture = load_texture(renderer, "food.bmp");
    SDL_Texture *background_texture = load_texture(renderer, "background.bmp");

    // Load level
    int **level = load_level("level.txt", &rows, &cols);

    // Initialize snake
    Snake snake;
    snake.body = malloc(INITIAL_LENGTH * sizeof(SDL_Point));
    for (int i = 0; i < INITIAL_LENGTH; i++) {
        snake.body[i] = (SDL_Point){SCREEN_WIDTH / 2 - i, SCREEN_HEIGHT / 2};
    }
    snake.length = INITIAL_LENGTH;
    snake.direction = RIGHT;

    bool running = true;
    while (running) {
        handle_input(&snake);
        update_game(&snake, level);
        render_frame(renderer, level, snake, food_texture, background_texture);
        SDL_Delay(1000 / 60); // 60 FPS
    }

    // Clean up
    SDL_DestroyRenderer(renderer);
    SDL_DestroyWindow(window);
    SDL_Quit();
    return 0;
}
```

