Certainly! In LaTeX, you can automatically generate a **Table of Contents (ToC)** using the `\tableofcontents` command. This command is typically placed in the document after the `\section` and `\subsection` commands have been used. LaTeX will then automatically generate the ToC based on the sectioning commands in your document.

Below is a complete example of a LaTeX document that includes an automatically generated Table of Contents. This example includes the necessary commands and structure for a standard LaTeX document.

```latex
\documentclass{article}

% For automatic table of contents
\usepackage{titlesec} % Optional: for customizing section titles
\usepackage{tocloft}  % Optional: for more control over ToC appearance

